==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extirpation
<hw>Ex`tir*pa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>extirpatio</ets>, <ets>exstirpatio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>extirpation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of extirpating or rooting
out, or the state of being extirpated; eradication; excision; total
destruction; <as>as, the <ex>extirpation</ex> of weeds from land, of
evil from the heart, of a race of men, of heresy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extirpative</ent>⟦br⟧
